<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id79b51d64-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s3336"><num value="3336">§ 3336.</num><heading> Special provision</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">On the date the Secretary approves the program under <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s3333">section 3333 of this title</ref>, the State shall be treated as having expended such portion of $32,000,000 as the State deems appropriate for purposes of implementing the program.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id79b51d65-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/96/561/tI/s135">Pub. L. 96–561, title I, § 135</ref>, <date date="1980-12-22">Dec. 22, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/3285">94 Stat. 3285</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
